  "prompt": "How do you find out what your zip code plus four is?",
  "response": "To find out your ZIP+4 code:\n\n1. Look at your mail: Often, your full mailing address will include the ZIP+4 code.\n\n2. Check official mail: Bills, statements, or other official correspondence may display the full code.\n\n3. Use the USPS website: Go to https://tools.usps.com/go/ZipLookupAction and enter your address to find the full ZIP+4 code.\n\n4. Contact your local post office: They can provide you with the specific ZIP+4 code for your address.\n\n5. Use online ZIP code lookup tools: Many websites offer free ZIP code lookup services.\n\nThe ZIP+4 code adds four additional digits to the standard five-digit ZIP code, providing a more precise location within a specific delivery area.",
